A truly immaculate 4 bed detatached property in the lovely village of Virginia Water.  Decorated to a high standard with quality fixtures and fittings.

Bordering the county of Royal Berkshire and in close proximity to prestigious Wentworth, Ascot, Sunningdale and Windsor, Virginia Water is one of the most exclusive and sought after addresses in Surrey. With its mainline rail service linking Reading to London Waterloo and easy access to the A30, M3 and M25 networks, the village is highly appealing to commuters and yet is situated amongst some of the area's most outstanding countryside. Within a very short drive to the American schools at Egham and Thorpe. 

Virginia Water takes its name from the lake to be found in adjoining historic Windsor Great Park, initially created by William, Duke of Cumberland in the early 18th century as a royal pleasure lake. Extensive landscaping , the construction of a number of ornamental buildings and the prodigious planting of exotic trees and shrubs resulted in the formation of one of the most impressive and picturesque lakes in England. Last enjoyed by the future Edward VIII for speedboat racing, royal use of the lake declined after the 1930's and today the extensive wooded grounds and lakeside walks are open for the delight of all. 

Today, Virginia Water retains much of its leafy charm and the village provides a range of local shops for day to day living. Slightly further afield, Windsor, Reading and Camberley offer more extensive opportunities for shopping, with a hugh choice encompassing all the high street stores and a number of specialist boutiques and independent shops. Bars, clubs, theatre, cinema and restaurants also abound, whilst all the thrills of the West End are as little as 45 minutes away by train. 

Closer to home, golfing enthusiasts are extremely well-catered for, with three prestigious clubs in the area at Wentworth, Sunngindale and the Royal Ascot Golf Club. Each summer during Royal Ascot Week, the renowned racecourse comes into its own as one of the major highlights in the social and horseracing calendar, whilst the Guards Polo Club is a regular fixture at nearby Smith's Lawn. 
